The paper discusses federated learning, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). It also addresses privacy concerns, which falls under the category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). The proposed algorithm involves balancing the trade-off between privacy loss and model performance, which is a common theme in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data science (cs.DS). Finally, the paper presents empirical studies, which could be considered as a form of computational social science (cs.SI).
